HEADWORD: Sinistrorsal
<hw>Sin`is*tror"sal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sinistrorsus</ets>, <ets>sinistroversus</ets>, turned toward the
left side; <ets>sinister</ets> left + <ets>vertere</ets>,
<ets>vortere</ets>, <ets>versum</ets>, <ets>vorsum</ets>, to
turn.]</ety> <def>Rising spirally from right to left (of the spectator);
sinistrorse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

